<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>thick end of the stick, the • thin end of the wedge, the</xh5><p> <i>thick end of the stick, the</i>—(also: short end of the stick, the) the disadvantage in a bargain, contest, etc.: Don’t be cocky: producers always hold <u>the thick end of the stick</u> and you should know that.</p><p> <i>thin end of the wedge, the</i>—(also: small end of the wedge, the) a modest beginning which may lead to smth. greater: It is <u>the thin end of the wedge</u>—they will contaminate our agriculture and that contamination will self-perpetuate as time goes on.</p> </entry>
